      "writtenOn": "2018-04-09T15:59:55Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Even if flags don\u0027t change, the GPA\u003d\u003eHVA mapping may change. So I\u0027d create a function:\n\n static bool is_compatible_mapping(hax_slot *slot,\n                                   uint64_t start_gpa, uint64_t size,\n                                   void *hva, int flags) {\n     return slot-\u003eflags \u003d\u003d flags \u0026\u0026\n            ((uintptr_t)slot-\u003ehva - (uintptr_t)hva \u003d\u003d slot-\u003estart - start_gpa);\n }\n\nThen instead of flag_changing, we could use:\n\n bool mapping_changing \u003d !is_compatible_mapping(slot, start, size, hva, flags);\n\nMore on this below.",
      "revId": "ddda163c2c90788e4f216d53a2526cb409987995",
      "serverId": "85c56323-6fa9-3386-8a01-6480fb634889",
      "unresolved": true
    },
